%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ewhy%3C%2Fem%3E%20you%20want%20this.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20shortage%20of%20information%20about%20how%20to%20reach%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%3Efinancial%20independence%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20so%20you%20can%20retire%20early.%20However%2C%20these%20strategies%20usually%20focus%20on%20building%20%3Cem%3Ejust%20enough%3C%2Fem%3E%20assets%20through%20investments%20to%20provide%20a%20baseline%20annual%20income%20for%20many%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20the%20route%20I%20take%20with%20my%20financial%20planning%20clients%20who%20want%20to%20set%20a%20goal%20to%20retire%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20is%2C%20you%20won't%20be%20in%20a%20solid%20financial%20position%20if%20you%20scrimp%20and%20save%20for%20the%20next%2010%20years%20so%20you%20have%20enough%20to%20retire%20in%20your%2030s%20or%2040s%20and%20live%20off%20%2430%2C000%20or%20less%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20life%20(which%20could%20last%20another%2050%20to%2060%20years!).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20do%20we%20tell%20clients%20instead%20to%20help%20them%20retire%20when%20they%20want%3F%20We%20focus%20on%20three%20core%20concepts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBuild%20a%20robust%20plan%20rather%20than%20aiming%20for%20the%20bare%20minimum%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20define%20financial%20power%20as%20the%20ability%20to%20have%20freedom%20and%20choices%20over%20how%20you%20live%20your%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20design%20a%20plan%20that%20requires%20you%20to%20live%20on%20less%20than%20the%20median%20household%20income%20in%20the%20U.S.%20for%20half%20a%20century%2C%20you're%20left%20with%20an%20extremely%20limited%20set%20of%20options%20for%20what%20you%20can%20do%20with%20your%20money%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrankly%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbeyondyourhammock.com%2Fbulletproof-balance-sheet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehaving%20no%20contingencies%20in%20place%20is%20also%20poor%20planning%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20your%20health%20deteriorates%3F%20If%20you%20make%20a%20poor%20investment%20decision%20that%20costs%20you%3F%20If%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20simply%20exceeds%20what%20you%20planned%20to%20spend%20annually%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20clients%20want%20to%20retire%20early%2C%20we%20support%20that%20choice%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20want%20to%20build%20a%20%3Cem%3Erealistic%3C%2Fem%3E%20plan%20for%20doing%20so.%20That%20means%20we%20don't%20assume%20they'll%20be%20able%20to%20spend%20half%20of%20what%20they%20do%20now%20once%20they%20retire%20or%20that%20their%20current%20lifestyle%20is%20the%20one%20they'll%20%3Cem%3Ealways%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20happy%20with%20for%20all%20eternity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20are%20not%20the%20same%20person%20you%20were%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20unlikely%20you%20will%20be%20the%20same%20person%20as%20you%20are%20today%20in%2010%2C%2015%2C%20or%2020%20years.%20Don't%20lock%20yourself%20into%20lifestyle%20choices%20now%20that%20you%20may%20find%20unsatisfactory%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESave%20a%20very%20large%20percentage%20of%20your%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20how%20do%20you%20build%20financial%20power%20to%20support%20a%20plan%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20retire%20early%20without%20limiting%20yourself%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20contribute%20a%20%3Cem%3Esignificant%20%3C%2Fem%3Eamount%20of%20your%20current%20annual%20income%20to%20long-term%20investments%20to%20grow%20wealth%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20significant%2C%20we're%20talking%20about%20saving%20a%20minimum%20of%2030%25%20of%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-adjusted-gross-income-agi-taxes%5C%22%3Egross%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERealistically%2C%20that%20figure%20likely%20needs%20to%20be%20closer%20to%2040%25%20or%20ev