d%20a%20total%20of%2019%20Syrian%20government%20troops%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20Homs%20desert%20in%20central%20Syria%2C%20according%20to%20the%20UK-based%20Syrian%20Observatory%20for%20Human%20Rights%20war%20monitor.%20Wednesday's%20attacks%20followed%20another%20attack%20on%20a%20Syrian%20army%20convoy%20in%20Homs'%20eastern%20countryside%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnpasyria.com%2Fen%2F114627%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ekilling%20five%20soldiers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EISIS%20killed%20an%20estimated%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Fa%2Fworrying-signs-exist-that-is-is-growing-stronger-in-syria%2F7558782.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E84%20Syrian%20soldiers%20and%2044%20civilians%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20central%20Syria%20in%20March%2C%20making%20it%20the%20most%20violent%20month%20in%20the%20ISIS%20desert%20campaign%20since%20late%202017.%20Another%20attack%20on%20May%203%20killed%20an%20estimated%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.alarabiya.net%2FNews%2Fmiddle-east%2F2024%2F05%2F03%2Fisis-attacks-killed-15-pro-government-syrian-fighters-monitor-%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E15%20pro-government%20fighters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Another%20four%20Syrian%20troops%20were%20killed%20in%20another%20desert%20attack%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rudaw.net%2Fenglish%2Fmiddleeast%2Fsyria%2F29042024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20late%20April%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECoupled%20with%20the%20latest%20attacks%2C%202024%20has%20already%20seen%20the%20deadliest%20violence%20perpetrated%20by%20ISIS%20in%20Syria%20so%20far%20this%20decade.%20ISIS%20lost%20the%20territory%20it%20declared%20a%20decade%20ago%20in%20Iraq%20in%202017%20and%20Syria%20in%202019%20and%20it%20now%20lacks%20the%20fighters%20and%20revenue%20it%20had%20then.%20But%20it%20still%20has%20enough%20armed%20adherents%20to%20attack%20opponents%20in%20the%20splintered%20Syria%20civil%20war%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20recruit%20more%20to%20its%20cause%20of%20holy%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20attacks%20aren't%20a%20sign%20of%20growing%20ISIS%20strength%2C%20said%20Joshua%20Landis%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Middle%20East%20Studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oklahoma.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20several%20years%2C%20ISIS%20has%20been%20able%20to%20make%20regular%20attacks%20in%20the%20desert%2C%26quot%3B%20Landis%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIn%20particular%2C%20it%20has%20had%20success%20in%20killing%20Syrian%20soldiers%20on%20buses%20as%20they%20travel%20between%20Deir%20ez-Zor%20and%20Syria's%20major%20western%20cities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20same%2C%20the%20frequency%20of%20its%20attack%20has%20decreased%2C%20particularly%20in%20Iraq%20but%20also%20in%20Syria%2C%26quot%3B%20Landis%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20been%20active%20in%20killing%20Syrians%20who%20venture%20into%20the%20desert%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F04%2F10%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fsyria-truffles-war.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehunt%20for%20truffles%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Badia%20desert%20in%20Homs%20is%20known%20for%20its%20high-quality%20truffles%20that%20poor%20Syrians%20often%20venture%20in%20search%20of%20in%20February-April%20each%20year%2C%20many%20of%20them%20risking%20death%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20ISIS%20or%20the%20various%20landmines%20and%20explosives%20strewn%20across%20the%20area.%20In%20early%20March%2C%20ISIS%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rudaw.net%2Fenglish%2Fmiddleeast%2Fsyria%2F06032024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emurdered%2014%20civilians%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20collecting%20truffles%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELandis%20noted%20that%20the%20Syrian%20military%20is%20picking%20up%20its%20efforts%20to%20attack%20ISIS%20in%20the%20Homs-Palmyra%20region.%20He%20speculates%20this%20might%20be%20the%20reason%20for%20these%20latest%20attacks%20and%20subsequent%20deaths%2C%20which%20he%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20sign%20of%20the%20Syrian%20military's%20engagement%20with%20the%20problem%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20of%20state%20weakness.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20see%20ISIS%20making%20an%20important%20comeback%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Landis%20said.%20%26quot%3BISIS%20is%20a%20product%20of%20state%20weakness%20and%20the%20strength%20of%20opposition%20forces%20more%20generally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20government%20remains%20weak%20compared%20to%20before%20the%20civil%20war%20began%20in%202011%2C%20the%20opposition%20is%20also%20much%20weaker%20than%20at%20any%20time%20since%20then.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20comparative%20advantage%20of%20the%20Syrian%20military%20is%20growing%20stronger%20every%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Landis%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ISIS%20attacks%20are%20one%20of%20many%20crises%20in%20Syria%20and%20are%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20weakness%20of%20the%20regime%20and%20the%20factions%20fighting%20it%2C%20another%20Syria%20expert%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20group's%20ability%20to%20recover%20depends%20on%20how%20the%20conflict%20evolves%20and%20on%20future%20choices%20by%20other%20actors%2C%20including%20foreign%20governments%2C%26quot%3B%20Aron%20Lund%2C%20a%20fellow%20with%20Century%20International%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20it's%20killing%20more%20people%2C%20the%20Islamic%20State%20is%20still%20a%20very%20minor%20threat%20compared%20to%20what%20it%20used%20to%20be.%20They%20don't%20hold%20significant%20territory%2C%20they%20have%20no%20meaningful%20population%20centers%20under%20their%20control%2C%20and%20they%20keep%20losing%20top%20leadership%20figures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAside%20from%20a%20%26quot%3Bweak%20and%20disjointed%20opposition%2C%26quot%3B%20Lund%20noted%20ISIS%20remnants%20are%20fighting%20the%20Assad%20government%20and%20the%20Kurdish-led%20Syrian%20Democratic%20Forces%20while%20%26quot%3Bplaying%20cat%20and%20mouse%26quot%3B%20with%20rebels%20backed%20by%20Turkey%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20ISIS%2C%20increasing%20the%20level%20of%20violence%20is%20important%20as%20it%20creates%20both%20%26quot%3Ba%20perception%20of%20threat%20and%20momentum%2C%26quot%3B%20Lund%20explained%2C%20which%20can%20influence%20local%20populations%20while%20simultaneously%20maintaining%20the%20morale%20of%20its%20foot%20soldiers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BAll-out%20religious%20war%20is%20their%20raison%20d'%C3%AAtre%2C%20after%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Lund%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESyria%20is%20still%20riven%20by%20internal%20tensions%20ISIS%20would%20love%20to%20exploit%2C%20and%20their%20hand%20could%20be%20strengthened%20if%20the%20US%20follows%20through%20on%20a%20complete%20troop%20withdrawal%20from%20northeast%20Syria.%20That%20could%20give%20them%20an%20opportunity%20to%20reorganize%20against%20a%20weaker%20Kurdish-led%20Syrian%20Democratic%20Forces%20administration%2C%20especially%20since%20thousands%20of%20ISIS%20militants%20remain%20in%20SDF-run%20prisons%20and%20detention%20centers%2C%20where%20they're%20often%20being%20held%20indefinitely.%20ISIS%20already%20attempted%20a%20well-planned%2C%20coordinated%20prison%20break%20in%20northeast%20Syria's%20Hasakah%20in%20January%202022%2C%20which%20took%20the%20SDF%2C%20with%20US%20support%2C%20almost%20two%20weeks%20to%20suppress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EProfessor%20Landis%20noted%20what's%20left%20of%20the%20opposition%20forces%20receive%20little%20foreign%20funding%20compared%20to%20the%20height%20of%20the%20Syrian%20war%20in%20the%202010s%2C%20and%20any%20remaining%20funding%20they%20can%20get%20isn't%20%26quot%3Bat%20a%20level%26quot%3B%20to%20undermine%20the%20Syrian%20military.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20intent%20of%20Western%20governments%20in%20extending%20sanctions%20on%20Syria%20is%20to%20prevent%20the%20Syrian%20military%20and%20state%20from%20rebuilding%2C%26quot%3B%20Landis%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20the%20same%2C%20the%20Arab%20governments%20have%20normalized%20relations%20with%20Damascus%2C%20which%20will%20help%20it%20to%20rebuild%20its%20forces%20and%20better%20police%20the%20desert.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Syrian%20military%20does%20carry%20out%20combing%20operations%20in%20the%20Homs%20desert%2C%20ISIS%20remnants%20are%20far%20from%20Damascus's%20top%20priority.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Syrian%20government%20seems%20more%20focused%20on%20the%20Turkey-backed%20rebels%20and%20on%20the%20SDF%2C%20but%20that's%20just%20common%20sense%20from%20Damascus's%20point%20of%20view%2C%26quot%3B%20Lund%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20groups%20are%20a%20much%20bigger%20political%20problem%2C%20and%20they%20represent%20a%20bigger%20potential%20threat%20to%20Assad's%20rule%2C%20even%20if%20there's%20currently%20little%20fighting%20along%20those%20frontlines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Century%20fellow%20believes%20ISIS%20remains%20a%20%26quot%3Bserious%20nuisance%26quot%3B%20that%20will%20continually%20prove%20difficult%20to%20eradicate%20but%20only%20has%20%26quot%3Blimited%20current%20power%26quot%3B%20and%20future%20potential.%20Even%20if%20the%20group%20does%20manage%20to%20pose%20a%20%26quot%3Bserious%20menace%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20regional%20and%20international%20powers%20will%20likely%20intervene.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BAll%20things%20considered%2C%20I%20would%20not%20expect%20Damascus%20to%20prioritize%20a%20terrorist-listed%20rural%20insurgency%20over%20these%20other%20two%20hostile%20actors%2C%20both%20of%20which%20govern%20large%20chunks%20of%20territory%20in%20a%20state-like%20fashion%20and%20enjoy%20significant%20foreign%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20Lund%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThat%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20Islamic%20State%20is%20an%20insignificant%20problem%20for%20Assad%2C%20but%20let's%20keep%20things%20in%20perspective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisis-remains-threat-syrian-desert-5-years-after-territorial-defeat-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718655571000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f367a79b4bb1c001df533ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisis-remains-threat-syrian-desert-5-years-after-territorial-defeat-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Islamic%20State%20has%20lost%20its%20territory%2C%20but%20its%20fighters%20recently%20carried%20out%20the%20deadliest%20month%20of%20Syrian%20attacks%20in%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Paul%20Iddon)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisis-remains-threat-syrian-desert-5-years-after-territorial-defeat-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shahid%20gets%20nostalgic%20as%20Udta%20Punjab%20clocks%208%20yrs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718655322000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111066993%2Cimgsize-53240.cms%22%2C%22