div%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20home's%20construction%20cost%20%248%20million%20when%20it%20was%20built%20in%201897%2C%20according%20to%20Thome.%20That's%20over%20%24300%20million%20in%202023%20dollars%2C%20accounting%20for%20inflation.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223969%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Great%20Hall%20of%20Lynnewood%20Hall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c89fbed9a404d829e04a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224961%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Great%20Hall%20of%20Lynnewood%20Hall.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leland%20Kent%2F%20Abandoned%20Southeast%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20many%20of%20Lynnewood's%20original%20furnishings%20and%20decorations%20have%20either%20been%20removed%20or%20degraded%20over%20time%2C%20it%20was%20once%20a%20masterpiece.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWidener%20entrusted%20its%20design%20to%20Horace%20Trumbauer%2C%20a%20then-29-year-old%20architect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Lynnewood%20Hall%20Preservation%20Foundation%2C%20the%20home%20has%20a%20Florentine%20bronze%20front%20door%2C%20and%20its%20main%20hall%20features%20marble%20and%20Caen%20stone%2C%20a%20limestone%20extracted%20from%20nortern%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Duveen%20Brothers%2C%20famous%20art%20dealers%2C%20furnished%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20home's%20interior%2C%20providing%20carved%20wood%20paneling%20from%20a%20French%20chateau%2C%20furniture%20sourced%20from%20Versailles%2C%20and%20tapestries%20previously%20owned%20by%20European%20aristocrats%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20foundation%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ENo%20detail%20was%20spared%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20mansion.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225798%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20decorated%20ceiling%20within%20the%20mansion.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c8b5de079049018194af6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223865%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20decorated%20ceiling%20within%20the%20mansion.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leland%20Kent%2F%20Abandoned%20Southeast%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWidener%20came%20from%20humble%20beginnings.%20He%20began%20his%20career%20as%20a%20butcher's%20apprentice%20and%20later%20established%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20meat-store%20chains%20in%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20historical%20website%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhousehistree.com%2Fpeople%2Fpeter-arrell-browne-widener-1834-1915%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHouse%20Histree%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20started%20to%20build%20his%20wealth%20by%20receiving%20a%20%2450%2C000%20government%20contract%20to%20provide%20meat%20to%20the%20Union%20Army%20during%20the%20Civil%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20life%2C%20he%20helped%20start%20the%20Philadelphia%20Traction%20Company%2C%20which%20built%20public%20transportation%20systems%20in%20Philadelphia%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20Chicago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20a%20philanthropist%2C%20funding%20libraries%20and%20establishing%20the%20Widener%20Memorial%20Home%20for%20Crippled%20Children%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.phillyhistory.org%2Findex.php%2F2009%2F03%2Fthe-widener-mansion%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhilly%20History%20Blog%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWidener%20also%20collected%20fine%20art%20and%20had%20a%20gallery%20built%20in%20the%20home%20that%20featured%20numerous%20world-renowned%20paintings%2C%20including%20several%20by%20Claude%20Monet%20and%20Rembrandt%2C%20the%20Lynnewood%20Hall%20Preservation%20Foundation%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20assuming%20responsibility%20for%20the%20Widener%20art%20collection%20upon%20his%20father's%20passing%2C%20Joseph%20welcomed%20the%20public%20into%20the%20home%20from%201915%20to%201940.%20When%20he%20passed%2C%20the%20family's%20collection%20was%20donated%20to%20the%20National%20Gallery%20of%20Art%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Great%20Hall%E2%80%99s%20soaring%20ceilings%20are%20decorated%20with%20carved%20crown%20molding.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223994%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20ceiling%20of%20the%20Great%20Hall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c8c1b764df161125a1823%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224993%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20ceiling%20of%20the%20Great%20Hall.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leland%20Kent%2F%20Abandoned%20Southeast%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKent%2C%20the%20blogger%20who%20toured%20and%20photographed%20the%20mansion%20in%202019%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20home%20was%20unlike%20anything%20he%20had%20ever%20seen%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20place%20that%20you%20go%20into%20that's%20large%20and%20dark%20has%20a%20spooky%20vibe%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Kent%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20as%20soon%20as%20your%20eyes%20adjust%20and%20you%20explore%20with%20a%20flashlight%20or%20walk%20through%20areas%20where%20there's%20sunlight%2C%20you%20can%20really%20see%20the%20material%20and%20the%20beautiful%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20main%20architectural%20style%20of%20Lynnewood%20Hall%20is%20called%20Palladianism%2C%20according%20to%20Thome.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221243%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20ballroom%20%20in%20Lynnewood%20Hall%20as%20of%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c8cc7e079049018194c20%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221497%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20ballroom%20in%20Lynnewood%20Hall.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20Lynnewood%20Hall%20Preservation%20Foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vam.ac.uk%2Farticles%2Fpalladianism-an-introduction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPalladianism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20architectural%20style%20popular%20in%20England%20from%201715%20to%201760%2C%20drew%20inspiration%20from%20the%20works%20of%20the%20Venetian%20architect%20Andrea%20Palladio.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20architectural%20style%20is%20deeply%20rooted%20in%20Roman%20and%20Greek%20influences%2C%20emphasizing%20symmetry%20and%20classical%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMany%20rooms%20in%20the%20mansion%20are%20now%20empty%2C%20except%20for%20some%20vintage%20chairs%20or%20beds.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Another%20view%20of%20the%20ballroom%20in%20Lynnewood%20Hall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c8d30e079049018194c4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnother%20view%20of%20the%20ballroom%20in%20Lynnewood%20Hall.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leland%20Kent%2F%20Abandoned%20Southeast%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ornate%20gold%20molding%20in%20the%20Reception%20Room%20looks%20similar%20to%20the%20wall%20decor%20found%20in%20many%20rooms%20throughout%20Versailles.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESome%20of%20Lynnewood%20Hall's%20dozens%20of%20bedrooms%20were%20designated%20specifically%20for%20staff.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20governess%20suite%20in%20Lynnewood%20Hall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c8defe079049018194cae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20governess%20suite%20in%20the%20mansion.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leland%20Kent%2F%20Abandoned%20Southeast%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20room%20was%20a%20governess%20suite%2C%20typically%20reserved%20as%20private%20quarters%20for%20a%20woman%20hired%20to%20educate%20and%20mentor%20children%20in%20an%20affluent%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EA%20bathroom%20in%20the%20home%20reveals%20how%20wealthy%20people%20lived%20in%20the%20early%201900s.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bathroom%20in%20the%20Lynnewood%20Hall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c8e9fed9a404d829e07e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20bathroom%20in%20the%20Lynnewood%20Hall%20as%20of%202019.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leland%20Kent%2F%20Abandoned%20Southeast%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20lavish%20bathroom%20features%20towering%20archways%2C%20polished%20mirrors%2C%20decorative%20molding%2C%20and%20a%20sizable%20marble%20tub.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EA%20guest%20bedroom%20on%20the%20second%20floor%20of%20the%20west%20wing%20had%20dusty%20furniture%20and%20a%20broken%20ceiling.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bedroom%20in%20Lynnewood%20Hall%20as%20of%202019.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c8fb2764df161125a19f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20the%20mansion's%20many%20bedrooms.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leland%20Kent%2FAbandoned%20Southeast%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20primary%20living%20spaces%20for%20the%20Wideners%20were%20located%20in%20the%20west%20and%20east%20wings%20of%20the%20second%20floor%2C%20at%20the%20front%20of%20the%20house.%20Housing%20for%20the%20domestic%20staff%20was%20in%20the%20basement%2C%20on%20the%20first%20floor%2C%20and%20extended%20to%20the%20third%20and%20fourth%20floors.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESeveral%20rooms%20contain%20old%20suitcases%20and%20books%20left%20behind%20by%20former%20occupants.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20deteriorated%20room%20in%20Lynnewood%20Hall%20as%20of%202019.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c91bee079049018194f59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20deteriorated%20room%20in%20the%20mansion.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of