m%2F654529763cc84b4dfafc0d5d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAerial%20view%20of%20traffic%20moving%20on%20Golden%20Gate%20Bridge%20during%20sunset%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California.%3Cp%3Esimonkr%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20not%20always%20see%20it%20through%20San%20Francisco's%20famous%20fog%2C%20but%20the%20now-famous%20hue%20was%20inspired%20by%20the%20red%20primer%20used%20for%20the%20bridge's%20steel%20beams%20and%20was%20officially%20selected%20by%20consulting%20architect%20Irving%20Morrow.%20The%20particular%20color%20is%20custom-made%2C%20according%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sherwin-williams.com%2Farchitects-specifiers-designers%2Finspiration%2Fstir%2FSW-ART-STIR-SAN-FRAN-RED%5C%22%3E%20Sherwin-Williams.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20you're%20wondering%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2011%2F04%2F26%2F135150942%2Fthe-golden-gate-bridges-accidental-color%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENPR%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20in%202011%20that%20it%20takes%20between%205%2C000%20and%2010%2C000%20gallons%20of%20paint%20to%20annually%20retouch%20the%20bridge's%2010%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20steel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBefore%20London's%20Tower%20Bridge%20was%20built%20in%201894%2C%20pedestrians%20had%20to%20cross%20the%20Thames%20river%20via%20tunnel.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223301%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22construction%20of%20Tower%20Bridge%2C%20London%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ab94158095b11674d8b45f1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222569%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EConstruction%20on%20the%20Tower%20Bridge%2C%20which%20took%20eight%20years%20to%20complete%2C%20began%20in%201886.%3Cp%3EHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20432%20construction%20workers%20eight%20years%20%E2%80%94%20and%2031%2C000%2C000%20bricks%20%E2%80%94%20to%20build%20Tower%20Bridge%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Ftravel%2Fdestinations%2Feurope%2Funited-kingdom%2Fengland%2Flondon%2Fsouth-east%2Flondon-bridge%2Farticles%2FTower-Bridge-fascinating-facts-and-figures%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20The%20Prince%20of%20Wales%20(the%20future%20King%20Edward%20VII)%20and%20his%20wife%20officially%20opened%20the%20bridge%20at%20a%20ceremony%20held%20in%20June%201894.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20bridge's%20completion%2C%20one%20million%20people%20relied%20on%20the%20Tower%20Subway%2C%20a%20410-meter%20(1%2C345-foot)%20tunnel%2C%C2%A0to%20cross%20the%20Thames%20each%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EToday%2C%20more%20than%2040%2C000%20people%20cross%20the%20bridge%20every%20day.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226484%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tower%20Bridge%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ab94197095b11340d8b45f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224863%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Tower%20Bridge%20at%20night.%3Cp%3EChris%20Ratcliffe%2FGetty%20Images%20News%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bridge's%20open-air%20walkways%20were%20closed%20between%201910%20and%201982%20because%20they%20were%20frequented%20by%20sex%20workers%20and%20pickpockets.%20In%201982%2C%20the%20walkways%20were%20reopened%20in%20honor%20of%20the%20Tower%20Bridge%20Exhibition%2C%20a%20permanent%20exhibit%20about%20the%20bridge's%20history%20on%20display%20in%20its%20twin%20towers%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flondontopia.net%2Fsite-news%2Ffeatured%2Ftower-bridge-10-facts-figures-londons-tower-bridge-probably-didnt-know-birthday%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELondontopia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20construction%20of%20Barcelona's%20Sagrada%20Fam%C3%ADlia%2C%20designed%20by%20Antoni%20Gaud%C3%AD%2C%20began%20in%201882%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20still%20not%20done.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221487%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sagrada%20Famila%20construction%201940%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ab40b2f095b1121008b4605%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221115%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGaud%C3%AD's%20Sagrada%20Fam%C3%ADlia%2C%20circa%201940.%3Cp%3EHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFamed%20Catalan%20architect%20Antoni%20Gaud%C3%AD%20worked%20on%20the%20awe-inspiring%20Gothic%20and%20Byzantine-influenced%20cathedral%20from%201883%20until%20his%20death%20in%201926.%20By%20then%20he%20had%20only%20completed%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20building.%20Construction%20started%20under%20architect%20Francisco%20Paula%20de%20Villar%20in%201882.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIt%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20by%202026%2C%20just%20in%20time%20for%20the%20100th%20anniversary%20of%C2%A0Gaud%C3%AD's%20death.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222671%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22La%20Sagrada%20Familia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ab4114d095b1172008b4604%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222003%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20interior%20of%20la%20Sagrada%20Fam%C3%ADlia.%3Cp%3EDavid%20Ramos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20string%20of%20collaborators%20who%20picked%20up%20where%20Gaud%C3%AD%20left%20off%2C%20the%20Sagrada%20Fam%C3%ADlia%20remains%20under%20construction%20due%20to%20its%20intricate%20design%20and%20disruptions%20caused%20by%20the%20Spanish%20Civil%20War.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20current%20chief%20architect%20Jordi%20Fauli%2C%20the%20building%20reached%20its%20final%20stage%20of%20construction%20in%202015%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fentertainment%2Farchive%2F2015%2F11%2Fsagrada-familia-reaches-its-final-stage-of-construction%2F413476%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Atlantic%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20While%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-the-finished-la-sagrada-familia-church-in-barcelona-will-look-like-in-2026-2013-10%5C%22%3Ecathedral%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20by%202026%2C%20for%20the%20100th%20anniversary%20of%20Gaud%C3%AD's%20death%2C%20it%20might%20take%20some%20additional%20time%20to%20add%20the%20final%20decorative%20elements.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Gateway%20of%20India%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20constructed%20to%20commemorate%20the%20visit%20of%20King%20George%20V%20and%20Queen%20Mary%2C%20was%20completed%20in%201924.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20of%20the%20Taj%20Mahal%20Palace%20Hotel%20and%20the%20Gateway%20of%20India%20in%20Bombay%20(now%20Mumbai)%2C%20India%2C%20circa%201930.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65452cc6b788914e554feeee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EView%20of%20the%20Taj%20Mahal%20Palace%20Hotel%20and%20the%20Gateway%20of%20India%20in%20Bombay%20(now%20Mumbai)%2C%20India%2C%20circa%201930.%3Cp%3EThe%20Print%20Collector%2FHeritage%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20British%20royals%20arrived%20in%20Mumbai%20%E2%80%94%20then%20called%20Bombay%20%E2%80%94%20to%20be%20officially%20instated%20as%20the%20Emperor%20and%20Empress%20of%20India%2C%20the%20monument%20had%20yet%20to%20be%20completed.%20Instead%2C%20they%20were%20shown%20a%20cardboard%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuilt%20in%20the%20Indo-Saracenic%20style%20by%20Scottish%20architect%20George%20Wittet%2C%20the%20Gateway%20%E2%80%94%20which%20overlooks%20the%20Mumbai%20harbor%20%E2%80%94%20features%20a%20dome%20that%20soars%2083%20feet%20high%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mumbai.org.uk%2Fgate-way-of-india.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMumbai.org%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EToday%2C%20the%20Gateway%20of%20India%20is%20a%20major%20tourist%20attraction.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gateway%20of%20India%20is%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Mumbai's%20tourist%20district%20and%20is%20the%20city's%20most%20famous%20landmark.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65452baeb788914e554fece0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGateway%20of%20India%20is%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Mumbai's%20tourist%20district%20and%20is%20the%20city's%20most%20famous%20landmark.%3Cp%3EDanny%20Lehman%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20massive%20structure%20is%20the%20first%20sight%20that%20greets%20visitors%20who%20enter%20Mumbai%20by%20sea.%20For%20that%20reason%2C%20it's%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BTaj%20Mahal%20of%20Mumbai.%26quot%3B%20The%20real%20Taj%20Mahal%20is%20located%20in%20northern%20India%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Agra.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EErected%20in%201936%2C%20the%20Obelisco%20de%20Buenos%20Aires%20was%20built%20to%20celebrate%20the%20400th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20first%20founding%20of%20the%20city.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20the%20Obelisco%20de%20Buenos%20Aires%20in%20the%20Plaza%20de%20la%20Republica%20in%20Buenos%20Aires%2C%20Argentina.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65452dbcb788914e554ff067%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20view%20of%20the%20Obelisco%20de%20Buenos%20Aires%20in%20the%20Plaza%20de%20la%20Republica%20in%20Buenos%20Aires%2C%20Argentina.%3Cp%3EEarl%20Leaf%2FMichael%20Ochs%20Archives%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Buenos%20Aires%20was%20reestablished%20in%201580%2C%20the%20Obelisco%20was%20constructed%20to%20commemorate%20the%20400th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20first%20(albeit%20unsuccessful)%20founding%20of%20the%20city%20by%20the%20Spanish%20explorer%20Pedro%20de%20Mendoza%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FPedro-de-Mendoza%5C%22%3EBritannica.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20initial%20criticism%20and%20controversy%20surrounding%20the%20monument%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20it%20being%20erroneously%20blamed%20for%20the%20destruction%20of%20a%20historic%20church%20%E2%80%94%20Argentinians%20have%20come%20to%20embrace%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bsilver%20sword%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20stands%20221.5%20feet%20tall.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESituated%20in%20Buenos%20Aires'%20theater%20district%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20two%20major%20thoroughfares%2C%20the%20monument%20is%20a%20popular%20gathering%20place%20for%20national%20celebrations.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221421%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Argentine%20soccer%20fans%20Obelisco%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ab90bcc095b11990b8b4599%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArgentine%20soccer%20fans%20at%20the%20Obelisco%20during%20the%202004%20World%20Cup.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Argentine%20soccer%20fans%20congregating%20to%20cheer%20on%20their%20nation's%20team%20to%20festivals%20focused%20on%20the%20art%20of%20tango%20or%20artisanal%20ice%20cream%2C%20the%20Obelisco%20has%20seen%20it%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMount%20Rushmore's%20symbolic%20tribute%20to%20US%20presidents%20George%20Washington%2C%20Thomas%20Jefferson%2C%20Theodore%20Roosevelt%2C%20and%20Abraham%20Lincoln%20was%20seen%20as%20both%20patriotic%20and%20controversial.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222315%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lincoln's%20head%20under%20construction%20on%20Mount%20Rushmore.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65452389b788914e554fdb42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222987%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELincoln's%20head%20under%20construction%20on%20Mount%20Rushmore.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20idea%20for%20the%20faces%20on%20Mount%20Rushmore%20was%20Doane%20Robinson's%2C%20a%20South%20Dakota%20historian.%20He%20enlisted%20the%20help%20of%20a%20controversial%20sculptor%20(with%20ties%20to%20the%20Ku%20Klux%20Klan)%20named%20Gutzon%20Borglum%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fsordid-history-mount-rushmore-180960446%2F%5C%22%3ESmithsonian%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20get-go%2C%20it%20was%20vehemently%20opposed%20by%20the%20Native%20people%20in%20South%20Dakota.%20The%20Black%20Hills%20of%20South%20Dakota%2C%20where%20the%20monument%20is%20located%2C%20belonged%20to%20the%20Great%20Sioux%20Reservation%20and%20the%20Lakota%20Sioux%20people%20before%20the%20US%20government%20seized%20the%20land%2C%20and%20the%20mountain%20in%20question%20had%20been%20a%20sacred%20location%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20took%20years%20to%20garner%20enough%20support%20and%20eventual%20funding%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20from%20the%20federal%20government%20%E2%80%94%20before%20getting%20underway.%20It%20would%20cost%20%241%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIt%20took%20400%20workers%2014%20years%20to%20complete%20Mount%20Rushmore%2C%20and%20it%20was%20finished%20on%20October%2031%2C%201941.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Close-up%20view%20of%20Mount%20Rushmore%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65429a6f36d588dc55c856c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EClose-up%20view%20of%20Mount%20Rushmore.%3Cp%3Eblackestockphoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESculpted%20into%20the%20southeastern%20face%20of%20the%20Black%20Hills%20mountainside%2C%20each%2060-foot-high%20face%20was%20meant%20to%20represent%20a%20different%20aspect%20of%20America's%20democracy%20and%20exceptionalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20George%20Washington%20was%20associated%20with%20the%20birth%20of%20US%20democracy.%20Next%2C%20Thomas%20Jefferson%20symbolized%20US%20expansion%20with%20the%20integration%20of%20land%20from%20the%20Louisiana%20Purchase.%20Then%2C%20Theodore%20Roosevelt%20was%20representative%20of%20America's%20economic%20prosperity%20and%20last%2C%20America%20commemorated%20Abraham%20Lincoln's%20role%20in%20saving%20the%20nation%20from%20collapse%20following%20the%20Civil%20War%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D6b5ddcb73acea7c19f01e52c41242a6a51e9f5b6424a8220b39f4d4afb47de7f%26postID%3D5ab264a504813b2b008b458b%26postSlug%3Dfamous-landmarks-construction-2018-3%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nationalgeographic.com%252Fhistory%252Farticle%252Fthe-strange-and-controversial-history-of-mount-rushmore%5C%22%3ENational%20Geographic%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowadays%2C%20the%20patriotic%20memorial%20rakes%20in%20tourists%20by%20the%20millions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESituated%20between%2033rd%20and%2034th%20streets%20on%20Fifth%20Avenue%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20New%20York%2C%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20was%20the%20world's%20first%20building%20to%20exceed%20100%20stories.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222932%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20photo%20of%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20under%20construction%2C%20circa%201930.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6542a7aa3cc84b4dfafa16f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224235%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAerial%20photo%20of%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20under%20construction%2C%20circa%201930.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201928%2C%20what%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpresenting-a-history-of-the-astors-2012-4%5C%22%3EWaldorf%20Astoria%20Hotel%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Fifth%20Avenue%20was%20acquired%20by%20the%20Bethlehem%20Engineering%20Corporation.%20The%20building%20was%20torn%20down%20to%20make%20way%20for%20what%20would%20become%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2017%2C%201930%2C%203%2C000%20workers%20set%20to%20work%20on%20the%20103-story%20project.%20It%20took%20just%20one%20year%20and%2045%20days%20to%20complete%2C%20meaning%20they%20built%204.5%20floors%20every%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2013%2F07%2F11%2Fus%2Fempire-state-building-fast-facts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20officially%20opened%20in%20April%201931.%20Then-President%20Herbert%20Hoover%20illuminated%20the%20building%20by%20pressing%20a%20button%20%E2%80%94%20all%20the%20way%20from%20Washington%2C%20DC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Empire%20State%20Building%2C%20an%20icon%20of%20New%20York%20City%2C%20is%20the%20most%20photographed%20building%20in%20the%20world.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22New%20York%20cityscape%20seen%20from%20above%20with%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20in%20view.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6542a7d63cc84b4dfafa172b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20York%20cityscape%20seen%20from%20above%20with%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20in%20view.%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Spatari%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Empire%20State%20Building%20has%20been%20recognized%20as%20a%20national%20historic%20landmark%20since%201986.%20It%20has%20been%20the%20tallest%20building%20in%20New%20York%20City%20twice%20%E2%80%94%20once%2C%20upon%20completion%20in%201931%20until%201971%20when%20the%20World%20Trade%20Center%20was%20built%2C%20and%20then%20again%20following%20its%20collapse%20in%202001%20and%20until%20the%20new%20One%20World%20Trade%20Center%20was%20constructed%20in%202012%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20clear%20day%2C%20the%20two%20observation%20decks%20allow%20for%20sights%20up%20to%2080%20miles%20away.%20Many%20movies%20have%20also%20featured%20the%20iconic%20building%2C%20from%20%26quot%3BAn%20Affair%20to%20Remember%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BKing%20Kong%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3BSuperman%20II%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BElf.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20popular%20tourist%20spot%20sees%20more%20than%204%20million%20visitors%20every%20year%2C%20according%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.esbnyc.com%2Fabout%2Ffacts-figures%5C%22%3Eofficial%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EInitially%20known%20as%20the%20Boulder%20Dam%20during%20its%20five-year%20construction%2C%20Hoover%20Dam%20would%20become%20the%20highest%20dam%20in%20the%20world%20at%20the%20time.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223687%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20view%20of%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Boulder%20Dam%2C%20renamed%20the%20Hoover%20Dam%20in%201947%2C%20shortly%20before%20its%20completion.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6542cfde3cc84b4dfafa5c68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222765%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAerial%20view%20of%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Boulder%20Dam%2C%20renamed%20the%20Hoover%20Dam%20in%201947%2C%20shortly%20before%20its%20completion.%3Cp%3EHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20it%20fell%20upon%20the%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Reclamation%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20solution%20to%20p