own-at-englands-euro-2024-match-13154483%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20Why%20Is%20Vladimir%20Putin%20Going%20To%20North%20Korea%20To%20Meet%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20will%20travel%20to%20North%20Korea%20on%20Tuesday%20to%20meet%20with%20leader%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20in%20a%20high-profile%20visit%20that%20will%20showcase%20their%20deepening%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAFP%20takes%20a%20look%20at%20what%20we%20know%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20are%20North%20Korea%20and%20Russia%20friends%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20was%20founded%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20North%20Korea%20became%20close%20to%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20USSR's%20collapse%20in%201991%20left%20North%20Korea%20without%20a%20key%20benefactor%2C%20which%20helped%20trigger%20a%20widespread%20famine%20later%20that%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20shortly%20after%20he%20became%20president%2C%20Putin%20sought%20to%20renew%20ties%2C%20visiting%20Pyongyang%20to%20meet%20Kim's%20father%2C%20then-leader%20Kim%20Jong%20Il%20--%20becoming%20the%20first%20Russian%20leader%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20in%20the%20mid-2000s%2C%20as%20a%20permanent%20member%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%2C%20Russia%20supported%20UN%20sanctions%20on%20North%20Korea%20over%20its%20nuclear%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20took%20over%20from%20his%20father%20in%202011%2C%20he%20initially%20tried%20to%20strike%20a%20balance%20between%20Russia%20and%20North%20Korea's%20other%20key%20historic%20ally%2C%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Russia%20and%20North%20Korea%20have%20since%20drawn%20closer%2C%20with%20Moscow%20forgiving%20most%20of%20its%20ally's%20debt%20in%202012%2C%20and%20Kim%20travelling%20to%20Vladivostok%20near%20the%20border%20in%202019%20to%20meet%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20visit%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022%2C%20Moscow%20has%20become%20increasingly%20isolated%2C%20and%20is%20looking%20for%20friends%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Kim%20made%20a%20rare%20overseas%20trip%20on%20his%20bulletproof%20train%20to%20meet%20Putin%20at%20a%20Russian%20spaceport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Korea%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Ukraine%20claimed%20North%20Korea%20was%20shipping%20weapons%20to%20Russia%20for%20use%20in%20its%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20violating%20rafts%20of%20UN%20sanctions%2C%20in%20return%20for%20technical%20help%20with%20its%20nascent%20satellite%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20has%20denied%20this%2C%20calling%20the%20claim%20%26quot%3Babsurd%26quot%3B%20--%20even%20as%20it%20thanked%20Russia%20for%20using%20its%20UN%20veto%20in%20March%20to%20effectively%20end%20monitoring%20of%20sanctions%20violations%2C%20just%20as%20the%20UN%20experts%20were%20starting%20to%20probe%20alleged%20arms%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKim%20has%20also%20ramped%20up%20weapons%20testing%2C%20including%20a%20flurry%20of%20launches%20this%20year%20of%20cruise%20missiles%2C%20which%20analysts%20said%20North%20Korea%20could%20be%20supplying%20to%20Russia%20for%20use%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20North%20Korea%20was%20always%20in%20a%20position%20to%20ask%20Russia%20for%20military%20and%20economic%20assistance%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheong%20Seong-chang%2C%20of%20the%20Seoul-based%20Sejong%20Institute%2C%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20countries%20are%20%26quot%3Bcooperating%20equally%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20said%20Cheong%2C%20adding%20it%20was%20something%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bhoneymoon%20period%26quot%3B%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20in%20it%20for%20Kim%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Kim%20%26quot%3Bthis%20visit%20is%20a%20victory%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20Leif-Eric%20Easley%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Ewha%20University%20in%20Seoul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20summit%20with%20Putin%20will%20both%20%26quot%3Bupgrade%26quot%3B%20North%20Korea's%20status%20internationally%20and%20%26quot%3Bbolster%20Kim's%20domestic%20legitimacy%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20while%20Russia%20could%20not%20replace%20China%20economically%2C%20it%20showed%20that%20%26quot%3BPyongyang%20has%20options%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKim%20is%20expected%20to%20greet%20Putin%20in%20person%20at%20Pyongyang%20Sunan%20International%20Airport%2C%20likely%20accompanied%20by%20Kim%20Yo%20Jong%2C%20his%20powerful%20sister%2C%20and%20his%20teenage%20daughter%20Kim%20Ju%20Ae%20--%20who%20many%20experts%20speculate%20could%20be%20North%20Korea's%20next%20ruler.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Korean%20news%20agency%20Yonhap%20said%20that%20satellite%20images%20showed%20possible%20signs%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Blarge%20structure%26quot%3B%20being%20installed%20in%20Pyongyang's%20Kim%20Il%20Sung%20Square%20--%20potentially%20indicating%20preparations%20for%20a%20major%20event%20or%20parade%20were%20under%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20the%20outcomes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20a%20Kremlin%20aide%2C%20Russian%20agencies%20said%20Monday%20the%20two%20leaders%20will%20sign%20%26quot%3Bimportant%20documents%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20include%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomprehensive%20strategic%20partnership%20treaty%26quot%3B%20which%20will%20outline%20future%20co-operation%20and%20deal%20with%20%26quot%3Bsecurity%20issues%26quot%3B%2C%20Kremlin%20aide%20Yuri%20Ushakov%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20state-run%20Russian%20news%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNorth%20Korea%20is%20placing%20its%20highest%20priority%20on%20relations%20with%20Russia%20and%20Russia%20is%20reciprocating%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Sejong%20Institute's%20Cheong%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%